05:41.858 --> 05:43.275
Niccolo Machiavelli wrote,

05:43.326 --> 05:45.277
"if an injury
has to be done to a man,

05:45.345 --> 05:46.778
"it should be so severe

05:46.830 --> 05:49.448
that his vengeance
need not be feared."

05:49.516 --> 05:52.017
Now, I thought Devil's Night
was Halloween Eve.

05:52.085 --> 05:54.620
The moniker "Devil's Night"
is somewhat deceiving.

05:54.687 --> 05:56.388
In Detroit, it's actually
a 3-day citywide

05:56.456 --> 05:57.556
cultural phenomenon,

05:57.624 --> 06:00.225
complete with masks,
chaos, and costumes.

06:00.293 --> 06:02.060
Say that 3 times fast.

06:02.128 --> 06:03.662
Yeah, a violent one.
Sounds like Mardi Gras.

06:03.730 --> 06:06.265
Vandals and amateur arsonists
literally set hundreds of fires.

06:06.332 --> 06:07.933
Who burns their own city?

06:08.001 --> 06:09.935
It started as pranks
in the 1930s

06:10.003 --> 06:12.471
but escalated in the 1970s
with disenfranchised youth.

06:12.539 --> 06:14.706
Well, given today's economy,
it must be a free-for-all.

06:14.774 --> 06:17.976
They've got record-breaking
unemployment and foreclosures,

06:18.044 --> 06:19.912
leaving a lot of displaced,
desperate people.

06:19.979 --> 06:21.413
And every single one
of these victims

06:21.481 --> 06:23.315
suffered
unimaginable pain.

06:23.383 --> 06:26.351
I'm sure that's what gets
him off, watching them burn.

06:26.419 --> 06:27.719
It gives him
power and control.

06:27.787 --> 06:29.621
The top of the whodunit
list is first responders.

06:29.689 --> 06:31.089
Firefighters,
arson investigators,

06:31.157 --> 06:32.424
cops, and paramedics.

06:32.492 --> 06:34.426
Civil servants
with a hero complex.

06:34.494 --> 06:36.295
All of whom
will be helping us.

06:36.362 --> 06:37.362
This guy's angry.

06:37.430 --> 06:38.363
Aren't they all?

06:38.414 --> 06:40.165
Not like this.

06:40.216 --> 06:42.467
Have you seen these?

06:42.535 --> 06:45.237
Extreme anger usually
manifests from a quick temper,

06:45.305 --> 06:46.305
but this guy's patient.

06:46.372 --> 06:48.340
I'm gonna ask Garcia
to notify us

06:48.408 --> 06:50.275
the minute that someone's
reported missing.

06:50.343 --> 06:51.843
Burns 3 people annually.

06:51.911 --> 06:53.912
It's like his Christmas.

06:53.980 --> 06:56.381
And the rest of the year
he just plans--

06:56.449 --> 06:57.716
targeting his victims
and then choosing

06:57.784 --> 06:59.217
the buildings
he wants to kill them in.

06:59.269 --> 07:01.253
There's a flaw in his plan.

07:01.321 --> 07:03.522
We know about it.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.190
We're stretched
as it is,

07:05.258 --> 07:07.292
but we've set up
a joint task force

07:07.360 --> 07:08.894
with the Detroit P.D.
to catch this guy.

07:08.962 --> 07:10.061
It's pretty extensive.

07:10.113 --> 07:11.563
I'd say don't profile me,

07:11.614 --> 07:13.064
but you're in a roomful
of suspects, right?

07:13.116 --> 07:14.533
A city full.

07:14.584 --> 07:16.568
Victims abducted across
every socioeconomic divide.

07:16.636 --> 07:17.970
And this son of a bitch

07:18.037 --> 07:20.305
is about to burn
a few of them alive.

07:20.373 --> 07:21.573
Problem is, we've
gotta catch up.

07:21.641 --> 07:24.242
And we know
he's gonna be watching.

07:24.294 --> 07:26.912
Well, we're gonna
bust him this year.

07:26.980 --> 07:29.314
We've got two agents on the way
to last night's crime scene.

07:29.382 --> 07:30.916
Great.
I'll meet them there.

07:30.984 --> 07:32.417
I hope we find
something soon.

07:32.485 --> 07:34.419
It gets dark early
this time of year.

07:34.487 --> 07:35.938
And we'll head to the morgue.

07:36.022 --> 07:37.889
Hope you have
a strong stomach.

07:44.314 --> 07:45.764
Gasoline was the accelerant?

07:45.815 --> 07:47.816
Gas vapors collect
in a low, enclosed space.

07:47.900 --> 07:50.936
When he ignited, those vapors
burned down to his bone.

07:51.004 --> 07:52.938
We call this
a fourth-degree burn.

07:53.006 --> 07:54.940
There's a fracture
on the back of his skull.

07:55.008 --> 07:55.941
That's right.

07:56.009 --> 07:57.643
Was that postmortem?

07:57.710 --> 07:59.911
No, it was antemortem bruising.
He was struck from behind.

07:59.979 --> 08:01.279
Blitz attack.

08:02.782 --> 08:04.249
What's this on her face?

08:04.317 --> 08:06.785
Charred fabric.
All of the victims

08:06.853 --> 08:08.387
have the same material
on them.

08:08.454 --> 08:10.756
The fire fused the original
garment to his flesh,

08:10.807 --> 08:13.592
then burned away,
leaving behind these remains.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.760
He's covering their faces?

08:14.827 --> 08:16.061
That's my best guess, yes.

08:16.129 --> 08:18.430
He doesn't want his victims
looking at him,

08:18.498 --> 08:20.165
even though we wants
to watch them die.

08:20.233 --> 08:23.068
It could be a sign of guilt
or inadequacy.

08:23.136 --> 08:24.269
Now, wouldn't a guy
like this

08:24.337 --> 08:26.571
want to see the terror
in their eyes?

08:26.639 --> 08:28.440
Instead, he keeps them
in the dark.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.676
He's covering their faces
and setting them on fire.

08:30.743 --> 08:33.445
It's an execution.

08:33.513 --> 08:36.782
It's easy to see
why he sets fires down here.

08:36.832 --> 08:38.850
It's completely isolated.

08:38.918 --> 08:41.285
He can beat, torture, or burn
somebody and nobody would hear it.

08:41.337 --> 08:43.154
I never thought the FBI
would be here

08:43.206 --> 08:44.823
for our fine
city's tradition.

08:44.891 --> 08:46.324
I'm Al Garner with the DFD.

08:46.392 --> 08:48.093
Agents Morgan
and Prentiss.

08:48.160 --> 08:50.429
I guess Devil's Night
keeps you pretty busy, huh?

08:50.496 --> 08:52.330
Not as much
as it did in the eighties.

08:52.398 --> 08:54.700
Used to get up to 600, 700
fires back then.

08:54.767 --> 08:55.867
In 3 days?

08:55.935 --> 08:58.003
Down to 115 last year.

08:58.071 --> 08:59.388
It still takes
everything we got,

08:59.472 --> 09:02.024
but fortunately
we've had some help.

09:02.108 --> 09:04.860
Have the police increased their
patrols in the Rivertown District?

09:04.944 --> 09:07.896
I wish they could, but the
city's reeling from budget cuts.

09:07.980 --> 09:11.733
No. Detroit's finest
is a community group

09:11.818 --> 09:13.985
with over a thousand
volunteers.

09:18.825 --> 09:20.158
A thousand volunteers?

09:20.209 --> 09:22.210
Well, that just added
another thousand names

09:22.295 --> 09:24.379
to Garcia's list.

09:24.464 --> 09:25.564
Do you think
he's one of them?

09:25.631 --> 09:26.998
Can't rule anyone out.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.513
What is this place?

09:41.581 --> 09:44.900
It's an old engine
factory.

09:44.984 --> 09:47.018
It's massive.

09:47.086 --> 09:48.420
And medieval.

09:48.488 --> 09:49.921
From
the industrial age,

09:49.989 --> 09:52.224
when this city was pumping
out more cars and hit songs

09:52.291 --> 09:53.759
than anyplace else
in the world.

09:53.826 --> 09:56.495
This is where we found
Tony's charred remains.

09:56.562 --> 09:58.697
The char pattern
tracks back to here.

09:58.748 --> 10:01.817
That's where he stood
when he started the fire.

10:01.884 --> 10:04.035
Not the best vantage point.

10:04.103 --> 10:06.438
There's your
escape exit.

10:06.506 --> 10:09.040
Yeah, except
he didn't want that.

10:09.108 --> 10:11.075
He needs to watch the show.

10:11.127 --> 10:13.078
This is the moment he's
been waiting for all year.

10:13.146 --> 10:15.680
One where he doesn't feel
inadequate or rejected.

10:15.748 --> 10:17.432
So he watches
as long as he can.

10:17.517 --> 10:18.934
Yeah, but fire's unpredictable.

10:19.018 --> 10:22.086
Every second in here he's
putting his own life at risk.

10:22.138 --> 10:23.722
And this guy's
obviously confident

10:23.773 --> 10:25.624
that he can get out of
here before it's too late.

10:25.691 --> 10:26.958
But there was
a fire alarm.

10:27.026 --> 10:28.627
My men were here
in 5 minutes.

10:28.694 --> 10:30.612
How?
And he knew it.

10:30.696 --> 10:33.298
This unsub doesn't leave
anything to chance.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.500
He knows exactly how long
he's got with his victims.

10:35.568 --> 10:38.904
He probably knows response times
or at least listens to them.

10:38.971 --> 10:40.472
Police dispatcher:
All units, be advised

10:40.540 --> 10:43.492
of a robbery in progress
at 9760 East Mills.

10:43.576 --> 10:45.744
Radio DJ:
This is your man DJ Cutz
with an instant blast.

10:45.795 --> 10:48.630
The feds are in town cracking down
on this year's Devil's Night.

10:48.714 --> 10:51.149
So I'd advise everyone
to stay off of the streets

10:51.217 --> 10:54.118
and keep them radios locked
to FM 99 Detroit.

11:10.019 --> 11:13.188
The first time I looked at these
victims on the map, none of it made sense.

11:13.272 --> 11:15.841
7 different victims, various
ages, sex, and ethnicity.

11:15.908 --> 11:17.442
What do you see now?

11:17.510 --> 11:18.443
The first victim...

11:18.511 --> 11:19.945
Often tells us the most.

11:19.996 --> 11:21.029
Tommy Proctor.

11:21.113 --> 11:23.147
Well, his rap sheet
is longer than the Nile.

11:23.199 --> 11:26.318
It looks like he's always
walked on the dark side.

11:26.385 --> 11:28.520
The first kill inspired him.
What's different about it?

11:28.588 --> 11:30.956
Two things. First of all,
his body wasn't found for days.

11:31.057 --> 11:32.858
He was buried
deep in the building.

11:32.925 --> 11:34.526
That often tells us
that they know each other.

11:34.594 --> 11:37.495
Not to mention it took many
botched attempts to burn them.

11:37.563 --> 11:39.297
Because the unsub didn't
realize how difficult it is

11:39.365 --> 11:40.799
to actually burn
a human body.

11:40.850 --> 11:43.535
Or it's overkill.
He wanted Proctor to suffer the most.

11:43.603 --> 11:45.770
Which definitely
makes it personal.

11:45.838 --> 11:47.639
If he knew the first victim, it's
a good chance he knew them all.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.140
We just have to
find out how.

11:49.208 --> 11:51.943
We can start by talking
to Tony Torrell's wife.

12:10.580 --> 12:12.597
How you doing?

12:12.665 --> 12:15.600
Uh...I'm fine.

12:15.668 --> 12:18.086
Uh, I'm here to see
Agent Rossi.

12:18.170 --> 12:20.772
He's going to be with you in just a few minutes.
I'm Agent Prentiss.

12:20.840 --> 12:22.007
Oh, I'm Kiersten Torrell.

12:22.058 --> 12:25.543
Uh...My husband Tony
was killed last night.

12:25.611 --> 12:26.544
I know.

12:26.612 --> 12:28.380
And I'm very sorry.

12:28.447 --> 12:30.115
May I sit down?

12:30.182 --> 12:32.183
Oh, yeah.

12:36.989 --> 12:38.890
Are--are you working
on his case?

12:38.958 --> 12:41.059
Yes, I am.

12:42.295 --> 12:45.447
Is there a picture
of him in your folder?

12:45.531 --> 12:47.799
I want to see him.

12:51.287 --> 12:54.372
Kiersten, uh, your husband
was very badly burned.

12:54.440 --> 12:57.242
I don't think
that's a good idea.

12:57.310 --> 13:00.378
What do you mean,
he was burnt?

13:01.480 --> 13:04.482
The person who did this
uses fire as a weapon.

13:04.550 --> 13:07.252
Was Tony set on fire alive?

13:07.320 --> 13:08.920
We don't know that--

13:08.971 --> 13:10.255
Oh, my God.

13:10.323 --> 13:13.658
Oh, my God,
this can't be happening.

13:15.695 --> 13:19.097
Ohh...Next week
was our anniversary.

13:19.165 --> 13:21.266
I'm so sorry.

13:21.334 --> 13:23.435
Are you married?

13:23.502 --> 13:26.738
No, I'm not,
and I can't imagine

13:26.789 --> 13:28.807
what you're going through.

13:28.874 --> 13:31.643
But everything you tell us

13:31.711 --> 13:34.746
can help us find the person
who did this to Tony.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.414
I know this is hard,

13:36.482 --> 13:38.450
but I want you to try
to remember that

13:38.517 --> 13:40.485
when you're talking
to Agent Rossi.

13:40.553 --> 13:42.520
Mm-hmm.

13:46.058 --> 13:50.996
Now, I'd like you to close
your eyes and relax.

13:51.063 --> 13:53.298
I want to walk you
through an exercise

13:53.366 --> 13:55.100
that's going to
help you recall

13:55.167 --> 13:56.968
everything that happened
last night.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.370
No, no, no.
What, like hypnosis?

13:58.437 --> 14:00.238
Not at all.

14:00.306 --> 14:02.507
Now, just close
your eyes

14:02.575 --> 14:06.544
and do the best
that you can. Ok?

14:06.612 --> 14:08.213
All right.

14:08.280 --> 14:09.881
Think about last night.

14:09.949 --> 14:12.584
You and Tony, you went to the
Halloween FItestival in Greektown.

14:12.651 --> 14:14.586
What time was it?

14:14.653 --> 14:16.254
Uh, around 9:30.

14:16.322 --> 14:18.089
Crowded?

14:23.095 --> 14:24.529
Yeah.

14:24.597 --> 14:28.767
Uh, there were drums
and loud music,

14:28.834 --> 14:31.603
some people wore costumes.

14:31.670 --> 14:33.938
Tony and I went
to the festival every year.

14:34.006 --> 14:36.107
We actually met there
when we were in high school.

14:36.175 --> 14:39.644
But this year we decided
not to dress up.

14:47.403 --> 14:48.903
Ohh!

14:50.022 --> 14:51.189
What is it?

14:51.257 --> 14:55.193
A kid dressed in a mask
jumped out, scared me.

14:55.244 --> 14:57.361
It made Tony laugh.

14:57.413 --> 14:58.830
Where's his mama?

14:58.898 --> 14:59.898
What type of mask?

14:59.965 --> 15:02.033
Uh, round, like a baby.

15:02.101 --> 15:06.037
