He was married
to Loretta Butler.

32:17.793 --> 32:18.860
Does he have
any children?

32:18.928 --> 32:20.044
Yes, they has one daughter.

32:20.129 --> 32:22.397
Her name is Tracy Anderson.
She was born in 1987.

32:22.464 --> 32:24.332
Why does she have
a different last name?

32:24.400 --> 32:28.169
When James' wife died, his sister
Susan Anderson adopted Tracy.

32:28.237 --> 32:30.054
And where is she now?

32:30.139 --> 32:31.239
She currently lives in Ohio.

32:31.307 --> 32:32.307
No, he says she's nearby.

32:32.374 --> 32:33.808
Where do the Andersons live?

32:33.876 --> 32:35.643
Uh, Indian Village.

32:35.711 --> 32:36.844
That's 3 miles away.

32:36.912 --> 32:38.580
Let's go.

32:38.647 --> 32:41.549
Here you go, hon.
I found a few more glasses for you.

32:45.921 --> 32:47.355
Tom.

32:47.423 --> 32:50.158
Oh, my God, Tom!

32:54.396 --> 32:56.798
Where is Tracy?

32:59.118 --> 33:02.337
Sorry. I keep trying the Anderson
house, but the line's busy.

33:02.404 --> 33:04.172
He must
already be there.

33:04.239 --> 33:05.673
Garcia, have any fires
been reported in the area?

33:05.741 --> 33:07.675
Negative, but medics and fire
suppression are on the way.

33:07.743 --> 33:09.611
Good.
Tell them to stand by.

33:09.678 --> 33:11.512
Roger that. Sir, there's
one more thing I gotta tell you.

33:11.580 --> 33:12.947
What is it?

33:48.917 --> 33:52.136
Now let's just get honest
with each other.

33:52.221 --> 33:53.721
Where's Tracy?

33:54.923 --> 33:55.857
She's not here.

33:55.924 --> 33:57.025
You're lying.

33:58.093 --> 33:59.794
I know she's back.

33:59.862 --> 34:03.698
Tracy's going to medical
school in Ohio.

34:03.766 --> 34:07.035
I don't believe a damn word
come out your mouth.

34:07.102 --> 34:08.969
We have no reason to lie.

34:09.038 --> 34:10.705
It's been 5 years, Kaman.

34:10.773 --> 34:12.607
She's moved on
with her life.

34:12.675 --> 34:14.509
Why can't you just accept that?

34:14.576 --> 34:15.743
Shut up!

34:36.197 --> 34:38.533
I'm calling backup.

34:38.600 --> 34:41.668
If anybody moves,
we're in trouble.

34:41.737 --> 34:43.638
We need a shooter.

34:43.706 --> 34:44.972
We're here.

34:45.040 --> 34:48.076
Your man wants everyone
to hold their position.

34:48.143 --> 34:50.043
We need a single rifle.

34:50.112 --> 34:54.181
I say again, all units,
hold your position.

34:54.233 --> 34:56.067
Copy that.

34:57.820 --> 34:59.404
This is the street.

34:59.488 --> 35:02.824
Hotch is going inside.

35:02.891 --> 35:04.542
And he's on his own.

35:04.626 --> 35:07.528
Hotch won't do
anything to spin him.

35:07.596 --> 35:09.197
It's not Kaman
I'm worried about.

35:09.264 --> 35:11.199
This isn't his first time
at the dance.

35:11.266 --> 35:12.834
We gotta trust him on this.

35:26.849 --> 35:30.618
Kaman,
why are you doing this?

35:30.686 --> 35:32.920
We never did anything
to you.

35:32.988 --> 35:34.021
You kept Tracy
away from me.

35:34.089 --> 35:36.624
Look what you've done.

35:36.692 --> 35:39.761
What you're about to do now.

35:39.828 --> 35:42.463
I wasn't always like this.

35:43.699 --> 35:47.435
People don't change, Kaman.

35:47.503 --> 35:49.537
This is all your fault.

35:49.605 --> 35:52.507
Baby, you can't keep blaming the
world for what happened to you.

35:57.846 --> 35:59.680
Baby, look at me.
Look at me.

35:59.748 --> 36:01.983
Kaman.

36:05.587 --> 36:08.523
What...

36:08.590 --> 36:11.025
What is going on?

36:12.394 --> 36:14.395
I needed to see you.

36:14.463 --> 36:17.198
And this is how
you do it?

36:21.170 --> 36:23.471
You abandoned me.

36:23.539 --> 36:25.907
You walked away from me
when I needed you the most.

36:25.974 --> 36:28.743
That's not good enough!
I'm sorry.

36:29.878 --> 36:31.379
After the accident,

36:31.446 --> 36:33.464
I had to get my life together.

36:33.549 --> 36:35.583
And what about my damn life?

36:35.634 --> 36:39.153
It took me 2 years
to get back on my feet.

36:39.221 --> 36:42.924
You were the only thing
that kept me going.

36:42.991 --> 36:45.993
Kaman...

36:46.061 --> 36:48.629
What happened to you?

36:48.697 --> 36:52.033
What do you think
happened to me?

36:52.100 --> 36:53.818
Mommy?

36:55.904 --> 36:57.505
Who else is here?

36:59.875 --> 37:02.176
Mommy, what's wrong?

37:07.499 --> 37:09.834
That's my sister's son.

37:09.918 --> 37:12.486
Uh, go back upstairs, baby.
Go back upstairs.

37:12.538 --> 37:13.654
Wait, wait, wait.

37:13.722 --> 37:14.989
He said mama.

37:15.040 --> 37:17.692
The boy's confused, Kaman.

37:19.928 --> 37:21.696
Is that your son?

37:21.763 --> 37:23.831
No, Kaman.

37:23.899 --> 37:26.868
Don't you stand in front of me
and lie to my face.

37:26.935 --> 37:28.469
Kaman, drop it.

37:31.440 --> 37:34.942
You shoot me, I drop this
and they burn. Then what?

37:35.010 --> 37:37.545
You move, you die.

37:37.613 --> 37:40.047
I'm already dead.
I ain't got nothin' else to live for.

37:40.115 --> 37:42.149
Tracy, you need
to tell him.

37:42.217 --> 37:43.818
Tell me what?

37:43.886 --> 37:46.521
What the hell's
going on here?

37:46.588 --> 37:48.489
He needs to know.

37:48.557 --> 37:50.558
Kaman...

37:50.626 --> 37:52.159
While you were in a coma,

37:52.227 --> 37:54.395
I found out I was pregnant.

37:54.463 --> 37:56.931
No...

37:59.902 --> 38:01.402
I didn't know
what to do.

38:01.470 --> 38:02.837
I thought
you were gonna die.

38:02.905 --> 38:04.272
Baby, I'm so sorry.

38:06.308 --> 38:09.010
You're telling me...

38:09.077 --> 38:10.745
That's my son?

38:13.415 --> 38:16.350
Kaman, you don't want to
do this in front of your son.

38:16.418 --> 38:19.153
Put it down.

38:19.221 --> 38:22.456
Baby, if you don't
do it for me, do it for him.

38:26.128 --> 38:28.996
Don't you want
to know his name?

38:48.650 --> 38:51.118
What's your name?

38:51.219 --> 38:54.956
Daniel Kaman Anderson.

39:28.924 --> 39:31.525
Thomas Kemp wrote,

39:31.593 --> 39:33.027
"love feels no burden,

39:33.095 --> 39:35.196
"thinks nothing of its trouble,

39:35.263 --> 39:37.315
"attempts what is
above its strength,

39:37.399 --> 39:40.501
"pleads no excuse
for impossibility,

39:40.569 --> 39:44.372
"for it thinks all things
are lawful for itself

39:44.439 --> 39:47.008
and all things are possible."

39:50.312 --> 39:51.846
Dad, don't look at me.

39:51.913 --> 39:53.681
I'm not looking.
Are you almost ready?

39:53.749 --> 39:54.682
Yes.

39:54.750 --> 39:55.883
Do you need any help?

39:55.951 --> 39:56.884
No.

39:56.952 --> 39:57.952
Ok.

40:00.122 --> 40:03.557
Whoa. That is definitely
not Spider-man.

40:03.625 --> 40:06.627
He's not a real superhero.

40:06.695 --> 40:08.763
He's not?

40:08.830 --> 40:10.297
Ok, I give up.

40:10.365 --> 40:11.565
Who are you
supposed to be?

40:11.633 --> 40:14.068
I'm you, daddy.

40:21.810 --> 40:23.310
Come here, buddy.

40:24.813 --> 40:26.897
Ok.

40:26.982 --> 40:29.417
Let's go get some candy,
my little G-man.

